  </nav>
  <aside class="source-note" role="note">
    <span class="provenance-label">Source note</span>
    <span class="provenance-text">
      The causal link between social media and mental health outcomes is
      contested in the research literature. Some researchers (notably Andrew
      Przybylski at Oxford) argue the effect sizes are small and the causal
      direction unclear. This is a live scientific debate, not a settled one.
      The correlation at the population level is real; the mechanism and
      causation are disputed.
    </span>
  </aside>
</article>
